<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-09T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-09T13:00:00-05:00" n="65" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d65">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/679: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Afghanistan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kabul</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-09T22:00:00+04:00">August 9,
                                    1942—10 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received August 11—7:49 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>50. Regarding airplane incident. In a signed note the Minister of Foreign
                            Affairs now states <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Although the trespass committed by an American airplane over
                                    Afghan territory has caused much concern to the Afghan
                                    Government the friendly action of the American Legation and its
                                    assurance that the trespass was not intentional have satisfied
                                    my Government and it accepts the expression of regret of the
                                    United States Government.</p>
                                <p>Trusting that all necessary precautions will be taken by American
                                    authorities concerned against the recurrence of such incidents
                                    in the future I consider the matter as closed.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>Repeated to Delhi.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>